<div id="review_3780292597" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3780292597" />
    <a title="J. Amill Santiago" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/77805242-j-amill-santiago"><img alt="J. Amill Santiago" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1588014369p2/77805242.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3780292597?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J. Amill Santiago" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J. Amill Santiago" href="/user/show/77805242-j-amill-santiago">J. Amill Santiago</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Pamphlet " href="/book/show/28584460-letter-from-birmingham-jail">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3780292597" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer910571362985235814">This is my second time reading this historic letter. It&apos;s long for a letter, but it takes about just one hour to go through it. Dr. King&apos;s rhetorical resourcefulness, rawness, passion, love, and authenticity bled through the pages of these letters to such an extent that it is impossible for me to remain unmoved as he described the injustices Black people were experiencing during the 1960&apos;s, and as he appealed to higher reason and logic, to eternal and God-centered realities, and to the emotions </span>
  <span id="freeText910571362985235814" style="display:none">This is my second time reading this historic letter. It's long for a letter, but it takes about just one hour to go through it. Dr. King's rhetorical resourcefulness, rawness, passion, love, and authenticity bled through the pages of these letters to such an extent that it is impossible for me to remain unmoved as he described the injustices Black people were experiencing during the 1960's, and as he appealed to higher reason and logic, to eternal and God-centered realities, and to the emotions of his opponents; citing their own secular and religious prophets, and dismantling their arguments and counter arguments with zeal and power, aided by the unyielding force of reason and passion. <br /><br />I will make the commitment to attempt to go through this letter every year. This second round was so much fruitful than the first, as I have become more familiar with the historical context and the contents of the letter. It is so much worth it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="910571362985235814" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
